issue_body:
Kinda new to python and django so I apologize if this is a noobish question.  How would I serialize this following related models using Serpy instead of DRF ModelSerializer and then use the serpy serializer in a DRF ModelViewSet?

**Models:**
```python
class Person(models.Model):
    first_name = models.CharField(_("First Name"), max_length=128, null=True)
    middle_name = models.CharField(_("Middle Name"), max_length=128, blank=True, null=True)
    last_name = models.CharField(_("Last Name"), max_length=128, null=True)
    email = models.EmailField(_("Email"), blank=True, null=True)

    def __unicode__ (self):
        return '%s: %s %s %s' % (self.id, self.first_name, self.middle_name, self.last_name)

class Bookmark(models.Model):
    person = models.ForeignKey(Person, related_name='bookmarks', on_delete=models.CASCADE)
    title = models.CharField(_("Title"), max_length=9999, blank=True, null=True)
    url = models.URLField(_("Url"), max_length=9999, blank=True, null=True)

    def __unicode__ (self):
        return '%s %s' % (self.title, self.url)
```

**DRF ModelSerializers:**
```python
class BookmarkSerializer(ModelSerializer):
    class Meta:
        model = Bookmark
        fields = ('id', 'title', 'url', 'person')

class PersonSerializer(ModelSerializer):
    bookmarks = BookmarkSerializer(many=True, read_only=True)

    class Meta:
        model = Person
        fields = ('id', 'first_name', 'middle_name', 'last_name', 'email', 'bookmarks')
```

**DRF ModelViewSet:**
```python
class PersonViewSet(viewsets.ModelViewSet):
    queryset = Person.objects.all()
    serializer_class = PersonSerializer
```

I have a multi select drop down control as an external filter to my tablesorter table.

It works great if I just have a value selected in the multi select, or if I pick the value from the multi select first and then values in the other external filter controls.

But if I already have values in the other external filter controls and then select something from the multi select it clears out all my other external filters.

What am I doing wrong?
I think it is probably something to do with this line:
      $('table').trigger('search', [filters]);

Do I need to save the filter values first, then trigger the search and then restore the filter values?
If so can you point me in the direction of that documentation (I searched but couldn't find what I was looking for).

Here is the code for the multi select.
	
        $('.multilocation')
            .on('change', function(){	
  			var myLocations = "";
			var filters = [];
            filters[2] = $(this).find(':selected').map(function(){
                    return this.value;
                }).get().join(' or ~');
			myLocations += "~";  myLocations += filters[2];
			filters[2] = myLocations;
            $('table').trigger('search', [filters]);
		});		

Thank you

