Consider to add `--silent, -s` option to `bin/js-yaml.js` for silent output upon success. It makes it easier to parse a lot of files, for example from a bash-script, and only focus on those giving errors.

Something like this in `bin/js-yaml.js` would fix it.

```
cli.addArgument(['-s', '--silent'], {
  help:   'Do not output file upon success',
  action: 'storeTrue'
});

if (!options.silent) {
  if (isYaml) {
    console.log(JSON.stringify(output, null, '  '));
  } else {
    console.log(yaml.dump(output));
  }    
}
