line#250 in the `field.py` will throw error if `x` is a nested list while this is possible in some datasets. my suggestions is to replace 
```
counter.update(x)
```
with 
```
try:
    counter.update(x)
except TypeError:
    counter.update(flatten(x))
```
function `flatten` is defined as
```
def flatten(nested):
    for x in nested:
        if isinstance(x, (list,tuple)):
            yield from _flatten(x)
        else:
            yield x
```

